HEADWORD: Sirdar
<hw>Sir*dar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind. & Per.
<ets>sard⟦amac⟧r</ets> a chief, general; <ets>sar</ets> the head, top +
<ets>d⟦amac⟧r</ets> holding, possessing.]</ety> <def>A native chief in
Hindostan; a headman.</def> <rj><au>Malcom.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In Turkey, Egypt, etc., a commander in chief, esp.
the one commanding the Anglo-Egyptian army.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sire</ent>⟦br⟧
